Partition definition in SQL Server/Azure SQL exists in three objects:
Copy code

Partition Function
Partition Scheme
Table / Index using the scheme
To recreate the partitioning for cff_report, you must extract:
Copy code

1 Partition function
2 Partition boundaries
3 Partition scheme
4 Table index using scheme
Below are queries used by DB engineers to generate the scripts dynamically.
1 Get Partition Function Script
This shows the partition function name and boundary values.
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
pf.name AS partition_function,
pf.type_desc,
prv.value AS boundary_value
FROM sys.partition_functions pf
JOIN sys.partition_range_values prv
ON pf.function_id = prv.function_id
WHERE pf.name IN
(
SELECT pf.name
FROM sys.tables t
JOIN sys.indexes i ON t.object_id = i.object_id
JOIN sys.partition_schemes ps ON i.data_space_id = ps.data_space_id
JOIN sys.partition_functions pf ON ps.function_id = pf.function_id
WHERE t.name = 'cff_report'
)
ORDER BY boundary_value
Example output
Copy code

pf_cff_report
2023-01-01
2023-04-01
2023-07-01
2023-10-01
2024-01-01
Script to recreate it:
SQL
Copy code
CREATE PARTITION FUNCTION pf_cff_report (DATE)
AS RANGE RIGHT FOR VALUES
(
'2023-01-01',
'2023-04-01',
'2023-07-01',
'2023-10-01',
'2024-01-01'
)
2 Get Partition Scheme Script
Partition scheme maps function → filegroups.
Query:
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
ps.name AS partition_scheme,
pf.name AS partition_function,
ds.name AS filegroup_name
FROM sys.partition_schemes ps
JOIN sys.partition_functions pf
ON ps.function_id = pf.function_id
JOIN sys.destination_data_spaces dds
ON ps.data_space_id = dds.partition_scheme_id
JOIN sys.data_spaces ds
ON dds.data_space_id = ds.data_space_id
WHERE ps.name IN
(
SELECT ps.name
FROM sys.tables t
JOIN sys.indexes i ON t.object_id = i.object_id
JOIN sys.partition_schemes ps ON i.data_space_id = ps.data_space_id
WHERE t.name = 'cff_report'
)
Example script
SQL
Copy code
CREATE PARTITION SCHEME ps_cff_report
AS PARTITION pf_cff_report
ALL TO ([PRIMARY])
3 Identify Partition Column
Find which column the table is partitioned on.
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
t.name AS table_name,
c.name AS partition_column
FROM sys.tables t
JOIN sys.indexes i
ON t.object_id = i.object_id
JOIN sys.index_columns ic
ON i.object_id = ic.object_id
AND i.index_id = ic.index_id
JOIN sys.columns c
ON ic.object_id = c.object_id
AND ic.column_id = c.column_id
WHERE t.name = 'cff_report'
AND ic.partition_ordinal = 1
Example result
Copy code

table_name       partition_column
cff_report       report_date
4 Check Partitions and Row Distribution
This shows how many rows exist per partition.
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
p.partition_number,
p.rows
FROM sys.partitions p
JOIN sys.tables t
ON p.object_id = t.object_id
WHERE t.name = 'cff_report'
AND p.index_id IN (0,1)
ORDER BY partition_number
Example output
Copy code

partition  rows
1          10M
2          12M
3          11M
4          15M
Useful for validating data migration later.
5 Generate Complete Partition Script Automatically
This script generates partition function boundaries.
SQL
Copy code
SELECT
STRING_AGG(
'''' + CAST(value AS VARCHAR(50)) + '''',
','
) AS partition_boundaries
FROM sys.partition_range_values
WHERE function_id =
(
SELECT pf.function_id
FROM sys.partition_functions pf
JOIN sys.partition_schemes ps
ON pf.function_id = ps.function_id
JOIN sys.indexes i
ON ps.data_space_id = i.data_space_id
WHERE i.object_id = OBJECT_ID('dbo.cff_report')
AND i.index_id = 1
)
Example output
Copy code

'2023-01-01','2023-04-01','2023-07-01','2023-10-01','2024-01-01'
